      void extendDelay​(com.anylogic.engine.Agent agent, double dt)
      Extends delay for the given agent ( it is possible to pass null as an argument - in this case all delayed agents will be affected ).
      Note that this function has no effect for agents which have finished their delay and are currently waiting to be consumed by subsequent blocks (because of 'pull' protocol)

      This function is available only for timeout type Delay blocks.

      void resume​()
      Resumes previously suspended Delay (if was not suspended, throws error).
      After this method is called, all timeouts of agents being delayed are resumed, thus their timeouts totally get increased by amount of time spent between suspend() and resume() calls.
      Unblocks input port if there is a room for incoming agents.

      • suspend

        public void suspend​()
        Suspends this delay. Blocks input port - even if delay isn't full.
        Timeouts of agents already being delayed are suspended until the resume() function call.
        Agents which have already finished their delay (and waiting for acceptance at the subsequent block) - are free to exit at any time subsequent block gets ready to consume them.
        See Also:
        isSuspended()

      • resume

        public void resume​()
        Resumes previously suspended Delay (if was not suspended, throws error).
        After this method is called, all timeouts of agents being delayed are resumed, thus their timeouts totally get increased by amount of time spent between suspend() and resume() calls.
        Unblocks input port if there is a room for incoming agents.
        See Also:
        isSuspended()

      • isSuspended

        public boolean isSuspended​()
        Returns suspended status of this Delay block
        See Also:
        resume()

      • extendDelay

        public void extendDelay​(com.anylogic.engine.Agent agent,
                        double dt)
        Extends delay for the given agent ( it is possible to pass null as an argument - in this case all delayed agents will be affected ).
        Note that this function has no effect for agents which have finished their delay and are currently waiting to be consumed by subsequent blocks (because of 'pull' protocol)

        This function is available only for timeout type Delay blocks.
